      • convertSFCommand

        public static void convertSFCommand(byte[] data,
                                    int increase,
                                    RefObject<java.lang.String> maskStr,
                                    RefObject<java.lang.String> incStr)
        This function is used to convert the data string to the string in ^SF when the increment and decrement functions are to be used.
        Parameters:
        data - [in] The original string data.
        increase - [in] Increment or decrement. If there is a "Serial Number" to be printed, the barcode information will be changed according to the value change of Serial Number, with 0~9 loop for numbers, and A~Z or a~z loop for alphabets.
        maskStr - [in] Convert the source string to a string with only 'a', 'A', 'D', '%' characters.
        incStr - [in] Convert the 'increase' variable, based on the 'maskStr' string, into numbers 0~9, letters A~Z or a~z, or %.
